{#
/**
 * @file
 * Default theme implementation for a view template to display a list of rows.
 *
 * Available variables:
 * - attributes: HTML attributes for the container.
 * - rows: A list of rows for this list.
 *   - attributes: The row's HTML attributes.
 *   - content: The row's contents.
 * - title: The title of this group of rows. May be empty.
 * - list: @todo.
 *   - type: Starting tag will be either a ul or ol.
 *   - attributes: HTML attributes for the list element.
 *
 * @see template_preprocess_views_view_list()
 *
 * @ingroup themeable
 */
#}
{% if attributes -%}
<div{{ attributes }}>
    {% endif %}


  {#  <{{ list.type }}{{ list.attributes }}> #}

{% if rows.0 is defined %}
    <div class="homepage-eclairage-playlist-element hidden-xs hidden-sm">

        <div id="home-playlist-slick-carousel-{{ rows.0.content['#view'].args.0 }}" class="home-playlist-items container no-padding hidden-xs hidden-sm">
            {% for row in rows %}
                <div class="item-playlist-content">
                    {{ row.content }}
                </div>
            {% endfor %}

        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="homepage-eclairage-playlist-element hidden-md hidden-lg">
{# on différencie le carrousel du deskotp qui affiche tous les contenus, du swiper mobile qui n'en affiche que 6
Pour pallier au probleme JS qui fait qu'on ne peut avoir 2 slick carousel avec le meme ID, j'ajoute +100 à celui du mobile #}
        <div id="home-playlist-slick-carousel-{{ rows.0.content['#view'].args.0 + 100 }}" class="home-playlist-items container no-padding hidden-md hidden-lg">
            {% for row in rows|slice(0,6) %}
                <div class="item-playlist-content">
                    {{ row.content }}
                </div>
            {% endfor %}

        </div>
    </div>
{% endif %}

